en_117708_0	Finance Minister Ravi Karunanayake says the loan facility for leasing vehicles has been increased from 70 percent to 90 percent.
en_117708_1	Addressing a media conference held at the finance ministry today, minister Karunanayake said this decision would remain until the next budget is presented.
en_117708_2	The leasing facility to buy vehicles was granted in full before it was recently reduced to 70 percent by the current government.
en_117708_3	Consequently, prospective buyers had to pay 30 percent of the value of the intended vehicle over the counter.
en_117708_4	Minister Karunanayake said that the on-the-spot payment has now been reduced upto 10 percent with effect from today.
